{{Infobox park | name = Kalsnava Arboretum | photo = Ūdens rozes Kalsnavas arborētumā - panoramio.jpg | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | type = Arboretum | location = [[Latvia]] | coords = {{coord|56|41|12.5|N|25|57|33.4|E|display=inline, title}} | area = {{convert|143.96|ha|acre}} | created = {{Start date|df=yes|1975}} | operator = | visitation_num = | status = | open = Yes | website = }}
'''Kalsnava Arboretum''' ({{lang-lv|Kalsnavas arborētums}}) is an [[arboretum]] in [[Madona Municipality]], Latvia.
The arboretum was founded in 1975 with the purpose "to conduct scientific research in dendrology and [[forestry]] and plant foreign woody plants for propagating purposes". It today contains some 2,500 different [[taxon|taxa]] and some 45,000 individual plants. The whole arboretum is protected as a nature reserve by Latvian law. The arboretum is a member of the Nordic Association of Arboretums and the Baltic Association of Botanical Gardens. The arboretum is open to visitors and offers a variety of services, including the sale of plants.<ref name=mammadaba>{{cite web |url= http://www.mammadaba.lv/en/objects/top-12/kalsnava-arboretum|title= LVM Kalsnava Arboretum|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date= |website= |publisher= Latvijas valsts mezi|access-date= 12 February 2017|quote=}}</ref><ref name=travel>{{cite web |url= http://www.latvia.travel/en/sight/kalsnava-arboretum|title= Kalsnava Arboretum|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date= |website= |publisher= Latvia.travel|access-date= 12 February 2017|quote=}}</ref>
