{{Infobox power station | name = Köthen Solar Park | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Germany | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|51|43|33|N|11|58|26|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = Germany | location = [[Köthen]] | status = | construction_began = May 2008 | commissioned = December 2008 | decommissioned = | cost = €133&nbsp;million | owner = | operator = | solar_type = PV | ps_units_operational = 205,000&nbsp;[[crystalline]] [[photovoltaic modules]] of [[BP Solar]] | solar_site_area = {{convert|116|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}} | ps_electrical_capacity = 45 [[Megawatt|MW]]<sub>p</sub> | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | ps_annual_generation = 42 [[GWh]] | website = | extra = }}
The '''Köthen Solar Park''' is a [[photovoltaic power station]] in [[Köthen]], Germany. It has a capacity of 45&nbsp;[[megawatt]]s (MW) and an expected annual electricity generation of 42 [[gigawatt-hours]]. The solar park was developed and built by RGE Energy.<ref name=exe>[http://www.exenewable.com/projectProfile.asp?id=14652 eXenewable Project Profile Page - Kothen, PV, Germany]</ref>
The PV project is built on a former military airfield in Köthen on {{convert|116|ha}}. In 2009, the project was the largest solar power plant in [[Saxony-Anhalt]] and the world's largest system using [[string inverter]]s. The project is equipped with 205,000&nbsp; [[solar module]] made of [[crystalline silicon]] by [[BP Solar]]. Total investment in the project was around €133&nbsp;million. The solar park was connected to the grid in 2009.<ref name=exe/><ref>[http://www.focus.de/fotos/ein-solarpark-auf-einem-ehemaligen-militaerflugplatz-in-koethen-dem_mid_1021762.html Ein Solarpark auf einem ehemaligen Militärflugplatz in Köthen. Dem Umweltministerium zufolge bringen die erneuerbaren Energiequellen Versorgungssicherheit.] {{de icon}}</ref> Payment was fixed to 35.49 Euro-cents per [[kilowatt-hour]] for 20 years.<ref>[http://www.photovoltaik-im-web.de/Solarpark_Koethen.pdf Solaranlage „Flugplatz Köthen“ in Sachsen-Anhalt] {{de icon}}</ref>
